                'content'          => '<h2>Eligibility Criteria</h2><p>To ensure a smooth academic journey, HS Global Academy has defined clear eligibility criteria for each stage of admission.</p><h3>Age Eligibility</h3><table><thead><tr><th>Class</th><th>Age as on 1st April</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Nursery</td><td>3 years to 4 years</td></tr><tr><td>LKG</td><td>4 years to 5 years</td></tr><tr><td>UKG</td><td>5 years to 6 years</td></tr><tr><td>Class I</td><td>6 years to 7 years</td></tr><tr><td>Class II onwards</td><td>As per previous class pass certificate</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Academic Eligibility</h3><ul><li>For <strong>Class I – VIII</strong>: No prior entrance test. Admission is based on age eligibility, document verification, and an informal interaction.</li><li>For <strong>Class IX</strong>: Transfer Certificate from a recognized school + Written Assessment in English, Maths, and Science.</li><li>For <strong>Class XI (Science)</strong>: Minimum <strong>60% aggregate</strong> in Class X with at least 60% in Science and Maths.</li><li>For <strong>Class XI (Commerce)</strong>: Minimum <strong>50% aggregate</strong> in Class X.</li></ul><h3>Documents Required at Time of Admission</h3><ul><li>Birth Certificate (original + photocopy)</li><li>Transfer Certificate (Class II onwards)</li><li>Previous Class Report Card / Marksheet</li><li>4 Passport-size photographs</li><li>2 Passport-size photographs of each parent</li><li>Aadhaar Card of student and parents (photocopy)</li><li>Address Proof (photocopy)</li><li>Medical Fitness Certificate</li></ul><h3>Reservation</h3><p>As per the Right to Education (RTE) Act, <strong>25% seats</strong> in entry-level classes (Nursery, LKG, Class I) are reserved for students from economically weaker sections (EWS) and disadvantaged groups. RTE admissions are governed by norms set by the District Education Office.</p>',
