                'slug'             => 'fee-payment-rules',
                'content'          => '<h2>Fee Payment Rules</h2><p>HS Global Academy follows a structured fee payment system to ensure transparency and convenience for all parents and guardians.</p><h3>Payment Schedule</h3><table><thead><tr><th>Fee Type</th><th>Due Date / Frequency</th><th>Mode</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Admission Fee + Caution Money</td><td>At the time of admission</td><td>Cash / Cheque / UPI / NEFT</td></tr><tr><td>Annual Composite Fee</td><td>April (1st Instalment) &amp; October (2nd Instalment)</td><td>Cash / Cheque / UPI / NEFT</td></tr><tr><td>Monthly Tuition Fee</td><td>By 10th of every month</td><td>Cash / Cheque / UPI / NEFT</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Payment Methods</h3><ul><li><strong>Cash:</strong> At the school fee counter between 9:00 AM – 1:00 PM on working days.</li><li><strong>Cheque / Demand Draft:</strong> In favour of <strong>"HS Global Academy"</strong>, payable at the school\'s city branch.</li><li><strong>UPI / QR Code:</strong> Scan the QR code available at the fee counter or school website.</li><li><strong>NEFT / Bank Transfer:</strong><br>Bank: State Bank of India<br>A/C Name: HS Global Academy<br>A/C No: XXXXXXXXXX<br>IFSC: SBIN000XXXX</li></ul><h3>Late Payment Policy</h3><ul><li>A late fee of <strong>₹50 per day</strong> is applicable after the 10th of the month.</li><li>If fees remain unpaid for <strong>two consecutive months</strong>, the student\'s name may be struck off the rolls.</li><li>Re-admission (if approved) will require payment of <strong>all outstanding dues + re-admission fee of ₹2,000</strong>.</li></ul><h3>Fee Receipt</h3><ul><li>A computer-generated fee receipt is issued for every payment.</li><li>Parents must retain receipts for the entire academic year for record purposes.</li><li>Duplicate receipts can be obtained from the accounts office on written request (₹50 fee).</li></ul><h3>Additional Charges</h3><ul><li>Transport fee: ₹800 – ₹1,500 per month (depending on route/distance).</li><li>Examination fee for board classes (X &amp; XII): As per CBSE norms (separately intimated).</li><li>Practical / Lab fee for Science stream (XI–XII): ₹500 per subject per year.</li></ul><h3>Refund &amp; Withdrawal</h3><p>One month\'s written notice or one month\'s tuition fee in lieu of notice is required for withdrawal. Caution money is refunded after clearance of all dues and library/lab items.</p>',
