                'name'             => 'Withdrawal / Transfer',
                'slug'             => 'withdrawal-transfer',
                'content'          => '<h2>Withdrawal &amp; Transfer</h2><p>HS Global Academy has a clear and fair withdrawal and transfer policy to assist families during transitions.</p><h3>Withdrawal Procedure</h3><ol><li>Submit a <strong>written application</strong> for withdrawal, signed by both parents/guardians, addressed to the Principal.</li><li>Provide <strong>one month\'s notice</strong> or pay one month\'s tuition fee in lieu of notice.</li><li>Clear all outstanding dues — tuition fee, library fines, lab charges, transport fee, and any other pending payments.</li><li>Return all school property — library books, lab equipment, sports gear, etc.</li><li>Collect the <strong>Transfer Certificate (TC)</strong> and original documents after 7 working days of submitting the application.</li></ol><h3>Transfer Certificate (TC)</h3><ul><li>The TC is issued <strong>free of cost</strong> if all dues are cleared.</li><li>A <strong>duplicate TC</strong> can be issued on written request with an affidavit and a fee of ₹500.</li><li>TC contains the student\'s personal details, dates of enrollment and withdrawal, class last attended, and a character / conduct summary.</li></ul><h3>Mid-Session Withdrawal</h3><ul><li>Parents withdrawing a student mid-session must pay the <strong>full session fee</strong> up to the quarter of withdrawal.</li><li>Caution money is refunded after deducting any outstanding amounts.</li></ul><h3>Transfer Within CBSE Schools</h3><ul><li>For students transferring to another CBSE-affiliated school, the TC and previous class marksheets are sufficient.</li><li>A <strong>Migration Certificate</strong> is additionally required for students transferring to a different board (State Board, ICSE, IB, etc.).</li></ul><h3>Refund Timeline</h3><table><thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Refundable?</th><th>Timeline</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Caution Money</td><td>Yes</td><td>Within 30 days after clearance</td></tr><tr><td>Admission Fee</td><td>No</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>Annual Charges</td><td>Pro-rated (if withdrawn in Q1)</td><td>Within 45 days</td></tr><tr><td>Tuition Fee (Advance)</td><td>Yes (adjustable against dues)</td><td>Within 30 days</td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>Note: The school management reserves the right to refuse a TC if the student has been involved in serious disciplinary violations pending investigation.</em></p>',
